# Spotify integration

## Auth

- Authorization Code with PKCE only. Never use client credentials or implicit flow
- Access tokens and refresh tokens stay server side. Never sent to the client
- Use httpOnly, Secure, SameSite=Lax cookies for session
- Refresh tokens automatically when expired. Clients should never see a 401

## API calls

- All Spotify calls live in `lib/spotify/`. No fetch to api.spotify.com from anywhere else
- Wrap each endpoint in a typed function: `getUserPlaylists()`, `getPlaylistTracks(id)`, `searchTracks(q)`, `createPlaylist(name)`, `replacePlaylistTracks(id, uris)`
- Handle Spotify rate limits (429). Read the Retry-After header and back off
- Return typed results, not raw API responses. Map to the `Track` domain type

## Scopes

Request the minimum: `playlist-read-private`, `playlist-read-collaborative`, `playlist-modify-public`, `playlist-modify-private`. Don't ask for `user-library-modify` or anything broader.